document.title: container-tools:3.0 security, bug fix, and enhancement update

notes.text:
An update is available for fuse-overlayfs, container-selinux, udica, runc, toolbox, podman, conmon, skopeo, crun, libslirp, oci-seccomp-bpf-hook, slirp4netns, containernetworking-plugins, buildah, criu, cockpit-podman.
This update affects Rocky Linux 8 from CIQ.
A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
The container-tools module contains tools for working with containers, notably podman, buildah, skopeo, and runc.

For detailed information on changes in this release, see the Rocky Linux 8 from CIQ Release Notes linked from the References section.

This advisory is provided by CIQ Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.
notes.title: Description

remediations.details:
Apply the security update for CRLBA-2022:0348 by updating the affected packages using your Rocky Linux from CIQ package manager.

For Rocky Linux from CIQ systems, run:
sudo dnf update

Or update specific packages:
sudo dnf update buildah buildah-tests cockpit-podman conmon container-selinux containernetworking-plugins containers-common crit criu crun fuse-overlayfs libslirp libslirp-devel oci-seccomp-bpf-hook podman podman-catatonit podman-docker podman-plugins podman-remote podman-tests python3-criu runc skopeo skopeo-tests slirp4netns toolbox toolbox-tests udica

After updating, verify the installed package versions are greater thanor equal to those specified in this advisory.
